values.title: CSCvd66153: fix heatmap dispay criteria
values.description:
Heatmap display criteria based on the mode of an AP 
is broken due to a bad code fix.

This fix corrects the problem.

Test Cases: (not all cases have been executed yet)
    1)
       Setup: Floor with AP1 in SE connect mode,
              AP2 in local mode with AQ enabled,
              AP3 in monitor mode,
              AP4 in sniffer mode
              AP5 is assigned but not positioned
       Step 1: unselect all APs
       Step 2: choose IDS heatmap
       Expected: IDS heatmap shown for AP3 alone

    2)
       Setup: Same as (1)
       Step 1: unselect all APs
       Step 2: select AP1 and AP4
       Step 3: choose IDS heatmap
       Expected: No heatmap is shown

    3)
       Setup: Same as (1)
       Step 1: unselect all APs
       Step 2: select AP1 and AP3
       Step 3: choose IDS heatmap
       Expected: Heatmap is shown for AP3 alone

    4)
       Setup: Same as (1)
       Step 1: unselect all APs
       Step 2: select AP1 and AP3
       Step 3: choose coverage heatmap
       Expected: No heatmap is shown

    5)
       Setup: Same as (1)
       Step 1: unselect all APs
       Step 2: choose coverage heatmap
       Expected: Heatmap shown only for AP2

    6)
       Setup: Same as (1)
       Step 1: unselect all APs
       Step 2: choose air quality heatmap
       Expected: Heatmap shown only for AP2

values.title: fix for that bug CSCvb89982
values.description:
issue:-
          while secondary is active, if pari (compliance) process down means Health monitor can't restart the pari process.so here this issue fixed.[pari process down means Health monitor restart the pari process].

Following Scenarios are checked if any process down means,health monitor restart the process.
-->standalone primary
-->standalone secondary
-->primary active
-->secondary sync
-->secondary active
-->primary sync

 HM check interval analysis:-
      Health monitor status check interval/retry  sleep time(5 secs) and retry(3 count)
      while Health monitor status check for every retry,it will take take following method execution time +5 secs
     checkDatabase();
     checkOOMError();
     checkNCS();
     checkRemoting();

values.title: DB maui fix bin sql scripts
values.description:
* aclProtocol.sql : Change syntax with sequences for Postgres

    Changes:
    seq_name.nextval -> nextval('seq_name')
    seq_name.currval -> currval('seq_name')

* delete_dup_job.sql : Change syntax for Postgres

    Change:
    - number -> numeric

    Add :
     - Change call of a anonymous block for Postgres (DO $$ ... END; $$)
     - declaration for var i and j with record datatype
     - IF EXISTS to ALTER TABLE comand

    Remove:
     - last commit
     - exit keyword
     - symbol /
     - rows "set serveroutput on" and "set line 200"

* Change:
    - view USER_INDEXES(Oracle) -> PG_INDEXES(Postgres)
    - Column name INDEX_NAME -> INDEXNAME
    - Column name TABLESPACE_NAME -> TABLESPACE
    - Add syntax for Postgres anonymous block (DO $$ .. $$)
    - dbms_output.put_line -> raise notice
    - TABLESPACE <> 'TS_IDX' ->
             upper(coalesce(TABLESPACE,'*')) not in ('TS_IDX','PG_GLOBAL')

    Remove symbol "/"

* ncs_api.sql : change syntax for Postgres

    Change
    - NUMBER -> NUMERIC
    - VARCHAR2(.. char) -> VARCHAR(..)
    - SYSTIMSTAMP -> CURRENT_TIMESTAMP

    Add IF EXISTS for DROP TABLE comand

    !!! HACK comment TABLESPACE

* updateVendorMac.sql: change syntax for Postgres

    Add:
    - var i_rec
    - Add syntax for Postgres anonymous block (DO $$ .. $$)
    - if exists for DROP comand

    Change:
    - number -> numeric
    - VARCHAR2 -> VARCHAR
    - dbms_output -> rise notice

    Remove:
    - symbol /
    - quit

* wcs_dropFKs.sql : Change syntax for Postgres

    Change ALTER TABLE comands
    - add IF EXISTS in DROP CONSTRAINT comands
    - remove "enable NOVALIDATE"
    - remove " symbols

    Comment "ALTER PROFILE" and "ALTER TABLE .. ENABLE ROW MOVEMENT" comands
    Comment using tablespace

* wcs_dropFKs.sql : Change syntax for Postgres

    Change:
    - number -> numeric
    - Add syntax for Postgres function declaration
    - dbms_output -> rise notice
    - Add vars rows_count, rec, rec1
    - recursive query connect by prior -> WITH RCURSIVE
    - SQL%ROWCOUNT(Oracle comand) -> get diagnostics rows_count = row_count;

    Remove:
    - symbol /

    !!!HACK Comment get_stale_tabs pipeline function because of using Oracle
    system package dbms_stats. TODO need to find out how to get list of
    stale tables.

* wirelessAlarmSpecificId.sql: Change syntax for Postgres

    Change
    - VARCHAR2 -> VARCHAR
    - ALTER TABLE .. ADD() -> ALTER TABLE IF EXISTS .. ADD COLUMN

    Remove default value for column, because cross-references to other
    columns in the current table are not allowed in Postgres

* wirelessAlarmSpecificId.sql: Change syntax for Postgres

    Add triger for generating value for column

values.title: BUG:CSCvd62634 CR:kkaliyan,bonagara SANITY:Yes Move updateSysCampusWithLocationGroupId() call to postInitialize, reduce postInitialize order from 0 to 1.
values.description:
Right now the order is:

 1st: 
   - Beans init from Spring context, including ConfigurationService and MapService
 Later (in no defined order since getOrder() on both hooks below returns value 0), via  XMPMainPostInitHook calls: 
   - NmsService.postInitialize() calling ConfigurationService.initializeDefaultInstances() doing SystemCampus SD creation
   - IfmGroupingDomainHook.postInitialize() doing System Campus LG creation

 What we need:
 a) create SystemCampus LG and SD like above by hooks having order 0
 b) tie SystemCampus LG and SD together by MapService. updateSysCampusWithLocationGroupId()

 for that:
  - in MapService move call of  updateSysCampusWithLocationGroupId() from init() to postInitialize()
  - make sure MapService.postInitialize() is called later than postInitialize() in NmsService and IfmGroupingDomainHook,
    for that change the value returned by MapService.getOrder() to something greater than 0
